The paper discusses a machine learning algorithm for combining different models, specifically neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of machine learning. The use of optimal transport and alignment of neurons suggests a focus on optimization and mathematical modeling, which are common themes in the subfield of machine learning. The application of the algorithm to convolutional networks, residual networks, and multi-layer perceptrons suggests a focus on computer vision and image recognition, which falls under the subfield of computer vision. The mention of transfer tasks and model compression suggests a focus on practical applications of machine learning, which could fall under the subfields of artificial intelligence, neural networks, and systems and control. Overall, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
